g cast members will be at the bottom of the list.-->\n}}\n| narrated                 = \n| theme_music_composer     = \n| opentheme                = \n| endtheme                 = \n| music                    = [[Siddhartha Khosla]]\n| country                  = United States\n| language                 =  {{Plainlist| \n* English\n* Spanish\n}}\n| num_seasons              = 1\n| num_episodes             = 1\n| list_episodes            = \n| executive_producer       = {{Plainlist|\n* James Chory\n* [[David Frankel]]\n* [[Becky Hartman Edwards]]\n* [[Peter Traugott]]\n* Rachel Kaplan\n* Assi Azar\n* [[Avi Nir]]\n* [[Alon Shtruzman]]\n* Elad Kuperman\n* Dean Georgaris\n}}\n| producer                 = Nick Pavonetti\n| editor                   = [[Elena Maganini]]\n| location                 = \n| cinematography           = [[Florian Ballhaus]]\n| camera                   = \n| runtime                  = 43 minutes\n| company                  = {{Plainlist|\n* Dean Georgaris Entertainment 2.0\n* [[Keshet Broadcasting|Keshet Studios]]\n* [[ABC Studios]]\n* [[Universal Television]]\n}}\n| distributor              = [[Keshet International]]\n| network                  = [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]]\n| picture_format           = [[1080i]] ([[High-definition television|HDTV]])\n| audio_format             = \n| first_aired              = {{Start date|2020|4|13}}\n| last_aired               = {{End date|present}}\n| preceded_by              = \n| followed_by              = \n| related                  = \n| website                  = \n| website_title            = \n| production_website       = \n| production_website_title = \n}}\n\n''''' The Baker and the  Beauty''''' is an American [[Romantic comedy|romantic]] [[Musical films|musical]] [[comedy-drama]] television series developed by Dean Georgaris that premiered on [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] on April 13, 2020.<ref name=\"SeriesPremiereDate\"/><ref name=\"Premiere Date Change\"/> The series is an adaptation of the Israeli romantic-comedy series ''[[Beauty and the Baker]]'' ({{Hebrewterm|\u05dc\u05d4\u05d9\u05d5\u05ea \u05d0\u05d9\u05ea\u05d4|Lihy\u00f3t It\u00e1h|\"Being with Her\"}}). The original version ranks as one of the highest-rated scripted series ever in Israel, and its episodes have been streamed on [[Amazon Prime Video]].<ref name=dea>[https://deadline.com/2018/10/baker-and-the-beauty-romantic-comedy-based-on-israeli-format-from-dean-georgaris-david-frankel-set-at-abc-1202485265/ \u2018Baker And The Beauty\u2019 Romantic Comedy Based On Israeli Format Set At ABC From Dean Georgaris, David Frankel & Keshet] Deadline. 18 October 2018</ref> The American version is being developed and executive produced by Dean Georgaris, [[Becky Hartman Edwards]], David Frankel, [[Avi Nir]], [[Alon Shtruzman]], [[Peter Traugott]], and Rachel Kaplan for [[Universal Television]].\n\n==Cast==\n===Main===\n<!--Main cast order is according to original broadcasting credits (the pilot episode). Do NOT rearrange cast order, per MOS:TVCAST. In addition, new main cast members will be at the bottom of the list.-->\n*[[Victor Rasuk]] as Daniel Garcia<ref name=\"Cast\"/>, a baker at his family's business who enters into a whirlwind romance with supermodel Noa Hamilton.\n*[[Nathalie Kelley]] as Noa Hamilton<ref name=\"Cast\"/>, a famous Australian model and entrepreneur attracted to Daniel.\n*[[Dan Bucatinsky]] as Lewis<ref name=\"Cast\"/>, Noa's manager who seeks to protect her image at all costs.\n*[[David Del Rio|David Del R\u00edo]] as Mateo Garcia<ref name=\"Cast\"/>, Daniel's younger brother and an aspiring [[DJ]] known as MC Cubano.\n*[[Michelle Veintimilla]] as Vanessa, Daniel's controlling ex-girlfriend.<ref name=\"Cast\">{{cite web|url=https://abc.com/shows/the-baker-and-the-beauty/cast|title=The Baker and the Beauty Meet the Cast|work=ABC Entertainment|accessdate=April 13, 2020}}</ref>\n*Belissa Escobedo as Natalie<ref name=\"Cast\"/>, Daniel and Mateo's younger sister who has high expectations placed on her by her parents.\n*[[Lisa Vidal]] as Mari Garcia<ref name=\"Cast\"/>, Daniel, Mateo, and Natalie's mother.\n*[[Carlos G\u00f3mez (actor)|Carlos G\u00f3mez]] as Rafael Garcia<ref name=\"Cast\"/>, Daniel, Mateo, and Natalie's father, and the owner of Rafael's Bakery.\n\n===Recurring===\n<!-- Reliably sourced and/or confirmed to make 4+ appearances in the series -->\n*[[Georgina Reilly]] as Piper, Noa's best friend and part of her entourage.\n\n==Episodes==\n{{Episode table |background=#000000 |overall=5 |title=26 |titleR=<ref name=\"TFC\"/>|writerR=<ref name=\"WGA\"/>|airdateR=<ref name=\"TFC\">{{cite web|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/showatch/baker-and-the-beauty/listings/|title=Shows A-Z \u2013 baker and the beauty, the on abc|website=[[The Futon Critic]]|access-date=January 13, 2020}}</ref> |director=15 |writer=22 |writerT=Teleplay by |airdate=15 |viewers=10 |country=U.S. |episodes=\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 1\n |Title           = Pilot\n |DirectedBy      = [[David Frankel]]\n |WrittenBy       = Dean Georgaris\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|13}}\n |Viewers         = 2.66<ref name=\"1.01\">{{cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-monday-cable-originals-network-finals-4-13-2020.html|title=Updated: ShowBuzzDaily's Top 150 Monday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 4.13.2020|last=Metcalf|first=Mitch|date=April 13, 2020|work=Showbuzz Daily|accessdate=April 13, 2020}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary    = On the night of his four-year anniversary, Daniel Garcia runs into Noa Hamilton, a famous model, shortly before his girlfriend Vanessa dumps him when he refuses her marriage proposal. Noa, claiming she feels bad for him, picks Daniel up and offers him \"three wishes\" for the night. They visit a restaurant owned by Noa's friend, where the two begin to realize how attracted they are to each other. Daniel uses one of his wishes to have Noa call his sister Natalie and offer her advice on how to handle starting a new school. While at a club, Noa's ex Colin tries to win her back. Her manager Lewis reveals to Daniel that Noa has a history of fooling around with strangers, and that she doesn't really love him. Daniel leaves in disgust and walks home, but discovers the next day that his family's bakery has dozens of new customers after Noa gave them a shout-out on social media. He then finds Noa waiting for him outside, saying she still owes him a third wish. \n |LineColor       = 000000\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 2\n |Title           = Ruin My Life\n |RTitle          = <ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/listings/20200406abc01/|title=(#102) \"Ruin My Life\"|website=The Futon Critic|accessdate=April 10, 2020}}</ref>\n |DirectedBy      = David Frankel\n |WrittenBy       = Dean Georgaris & [[Becky Hartman]]\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|20}}\n |Viewers         = <!-- Episode summaries must be expressed in your own words. Do NOT submit content you find from another web site as it is plagiarism and likely a copyright violation, which Wikipedia cannot accept and will be removed or reverted. Superficially modifying copyrighted content or closely paraphrasing it, even if the source is cited, still constitutes a copyright violation. Summaries should be about 100 to 200 words in length, per MOS:TVPLOT, and those substantially less than 100 words are most likely to be scrutinized for possible copyright violation. -->\n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = 000000\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 3\n |Title           = Get Carried Away\n |RTitle          = <ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/listings/20200413abc01/|title=(#103) \"Get Carried Away\"|website=The Futon Critic|accessdate=April 14, 2020}}</ref>\n |DirectedBy      = [[Joanna Kerns]]\n |WrittenBy       = [[Valentina L. Garza]]\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|27}}\n |Viewers         = <!-- Episode summaries must be expressed in your own words. Do NOT submit content you find from another web site as it is plagiarism and likely a copyright violation, which Wikipedia cannot accept and will be removed or reverted. Superficially modifying copyrighted content or closely paraphrasing it, even if the source is cited, still constitutes a copyright violation. Summaries should be about 100 to 200 words in length, per MOS:TVPLOT, and those substantially less than 100 words are most likely to be scrutinized for possible copyright violation. -->\n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = 000000\n}}\n}}\nEpisodes of the first season include:<ref name=\"WGA\">{{Cite web|title=The Baker and the Beauty|url=https://directories.wga.org/project/1192320/the-baker-and-the-beauty/|work=[[Writers Guild of America West]]|access-date=March 29, 2020}}</ref> \n*\"The Party and the Pastelitos\" teleplay by Dean Georgaris & [[Becky Hartman Edwards|Becky Edwards]]\n*\"Blow Out\" teleplay by Dean Georgaris\n*\"I Think She's Coming Out\" teleplay by Albert Torres\n*\"Honeymoon's Over\" teleplay by Sasha Stroman\n\n==Production==\n===Development===\nIn November 2018, it was announced that an adaptation of the series was being developed by Dean Georgaris and [[David Frankel]] through Keshet Studios and [[Universal Television]] for [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]]. The series is one of two collaborations between Georgaris and Universal for the 2019\u201320 season, along with ''[[Bluff City Law]]'' for [[NBC]]'s fall schedule.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/01/abc-the-baker-and-the-beauty-pilot-israeli-format-dean-georgaris-1202544051/|title=ABC Orders 'The Baker And The Beauty' Based On Israeli Format In Second Pilot Pickup For Dean Georgaris This Season|last=Andreeva|first=Nellie|last2=Andreeva|first2=Nellie|date=2019-01-28|website=Deadline|language=en|access-date=2019-06-10}}</ref> Georgaris and Frankel are set to write and direct, respectively, and both will executive produce alongside [[Avi Nir]], [[Alon Shtruzman]], [[Peter Traugott]], and Rachel Kaplan.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2018/10/baker-and-the-beauty-romantic-comedy-based-on-israeli-format-from-dean-georgaris-david-frankel-set-at-abc-1202485265/|title='Baker And The Beauty' Romantic Comedy Based On Israeli Format Set At ABC From Dean Georgaris, David Frankel & Keshet|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|last=Andreeva|first=Nellie|date=October 18, 2018|accessdate=November 9, 2018}}</ref> In January 2019 ABC ordered the adaptation to pilot.<ref>[https://variety.com/2019/tv/news/abc-the-baker-and-the-beauty-1203121008/ ABC Orders Pilot for Drama \u2018The Baker and The Beauty\u2019 Based on Israeli Series] Variety. 28 January 2019</ref> On May 11, 2019, ABC green-lighted the series.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/05/the-baker-and-the-beauty-israeli-format-dean-georgaris-abc-series-order-1202612578/|title='The Baker And The Beauty' Gets ABC Series Order As Dean Georgaris Scores Double|first=Nellie|last=Andreeva|first2=Denise|last2=Petski|website=Deadline Hollywood|date=May 11, 2019|accessdate=May 11, 2019}}</ref> A few days later, it was announced that the series would premiere as a [[mid-season replacement]] in the spring of 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/05/abc-fall-2019-20-schedule-upfronts-new-shows-the-rookie-mixed-ish-emergence-cobie-smulders-1202614248|title=ABC Fall 2019-20 Schedule: Very Few Changes, 'The Rookie' Moves To Sunday, 'American Housewife' To Friday|last=Andreeva|first=Nellie|work=from Deadline Hollywood|date=May 14, 2019|accessdate=May 14, 2019}}</ref> On January 8, 2020, it was reported that the series is set to premiere on April 6, 2020.<ref name=\"SeriesPremiereDate\">{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2020/01/midseason-moves-shark-tank-american-housewife-baker-and-the-beauty-premiere-date-tca-1202824384/|title=Midseason Moves For ABC's 'Shark Tank' & 'American Housewife'; 'Baker And The Beauty' Gets Premiere Date \u2013 TCA|work=Deadline Hollywood|first=Denise|last=Petski|date=January 8, 2020|accessdate=January 8, 2020}}</ref> On January 29, 2020, the premiere date was moved to April 13, 2020.<ref name=\"Premiere Date Change\">{{cite web|title=ABC Invites You to the Ultimate Date Night on Monday, April 13|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/news/2020/01/29/abc-invites-you-to-the-ultimate-date-night-on-monday-april-13-124412/20200129abc02/|work=[[The Futon Critic]]|date=January 29, 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Casting===\nIn February 2019, it was announced that [[Carlos G\u00f3mez (actor)|Carlos Gomez]], [[Lisa Vidal]] and [[Dan Bucatinsky]] had been cast in the pilot's lead roles.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/02/the-baker-and-the-beauty-carlos-gomez-lisa-vidal-dan-bucatinsky-cast-abc-comedy-pilot-1202567280/|title='The Baker And The Beauty': Carlos Gomez, Lisa Vidal & Dan Bucatinsky Cast In ABC Comedy Pilot|first=Nellie|last=Andreeva|first2=Denise|last2=Petski|website=Deadline Hollywood|date=February 28, 2019|accessdate=May 12, 2019}}</ref> Alongside the pilot's order announcement, in March 2019 it was reported that [[Nathalie Kelley]], [[Victor Rasuk]], [[Michelle Veintimilla]] and [[David Del Rio]] had joined the cast.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/03/nathalie-kelley-star-the-baker-and-the-beauty-abc-comedy-pilot-1202569310/|title=Nathalie Kelley To Star In 'The Baker And The Beauty' ABC Romantic Comedy Pilot|first=Nellie|last=Andreeva|first2=Denise|last2=Petski|website=Deadline Hollywood|date=March 4, 2019|accessdate=May 12, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/03/the-baker-and-the-beauty-victor-rasuk-star-abc-romantic-comedy-pilot-1202570274/|title='The Baker And The Beauty': Victor Rasuk To Star In ABC Romantic Comedy Pilot|first=Nellie|last=Andreeva|website=Deadline Hollywood|date=March 6, 2019|accessdate=May 12, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/03/abc-pilots-united-we-fall-stumptown-baker-and-the-beauty-leslie-odom-jr-jason-michael-snow-adrian-martinez-michelle-veintimilla-alexis-fields-1202573118/|title=ABC Pilots 'United We Fall', 'Stumptown', 'Baker & The Beauty' & Leslie Odom Jr. Comedy Add To Cast|first=Denise|last=Petski|website=Deadline Hollywood|date=March 11, 2019|accessdate=May 12, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/03/christian-borle-abc-until-the-wedding-david-del-rio-the-baker-and-the-beauty-1202576213/|title=Christian Borle Joins ABC's 'Until The Wedding'; David Del Rio In 'The Baker And The Beauty'|first=Denise|last=Petski|website=Deadline Hollywood|date=March 15, 2019|accessdate=May 12, 2019}}</ref> In September 2019, [[Georgina Reilly]] had been cast in a recurring role.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/09/maria-gabriela-de-faria-fox-a-moody-christmas-the-baker-the-beauty-casts-georgina-reilly-1202747019/|title=Maria Gabriela de Faria Joins Fox's 'A Moody Christmas'; 'The Baker & The Beauty' Casts Georgina Reilly|first1=Dominic|last1=Patten|first2=Denise|last2=Petski|website=Deadline Hollywood|date=September 30, 2019|accessdate=September 30, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Filming===\nThe pilot was filmed in [[Atlanta]] while rest of the series was filmed in [[Puerto Rico]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://popculture.com/tv-shows/2020/04/13/baker-beauty-lisa-vidal-recounts-extreme-conditions-filming-connected-cast-exclusive/|title='The Baker and the Beauty': Lisa Vidal Recounts How Extreme Conditions While Filming Connected the Cast (Exclusive)|first=Stephanie|last=Downs|website=Deadline Hollywood|date=April 13, 2020|accessdate=April 14, 2020}}</ref>\n==Reception==\n<!--===Critical response===-->\n===Ratings===\n{{Television episode ratings\n| width     = 99\n| noshare   = y\n\n| title1    = [[#ep1|Pilot]]\n| date1     = April 13, 2020\n| rs1       = 0.5\n| viewers1  = 2.66<ref name=\"1.01\"/>\n| dvr1      = \n| dvrv1     =\n| total1    =\n| totalv1   = \n<!--\n| title2    = [[#ep2|Ruin My Life]]\n| date2     = April 20, 2020\n| rs2       = \n| viewers2  = \n| dvr2      